---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Alert from '../../../components/Alert.astro';
import Tabs from '../../../components/Tabs.tsx';
import Collapsible from '../../../components/Collapsible.tsx';
---
<Layout title="MemoryGuard — Setup">
  <h1>MemoryGuard — Setup</h1>
  <p>MemoryGuard monitors heap usage in Node.js applications and alerts you to potential memory leaks in real time.</p>

  <Alert type="info">
    <p>MemoryGuard runs in a worker thread and has negligible impact on event loop latency. It's safe to use in staging and production environments.</p>
  </Alert>

  <h2>Installation</h2>
  <Tabs
    client:load
    id="install-mg"
    tabs={[
      { label: 'Yarn', content: '<pre><code>yarn add -D @memoryguard/agent</code></pre>' },
      { label: 'npm', content: '<pre><code>npm install -D @memoryguard/agent</code></pre>' },
    ]}
  />

  <h2>Adding the Agent</h2>
  <p>Import and start the agent at the top of your application entry point:</p>
  <pre><code>{`import { startMemoryGuard } from '@memoryguard/agent';

startMemoryGuard({
  sampleInterval: 5000,  // milliseconds
  heapLimit: '512mb',
});`}</code></pre>

  <p>Key configuration options at initialization:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>sampleInterval</strong> — How often to take heap snapshots (in ms)</li>
    <li><strong>heapLimit</strong> — Threshold for warning alerts</li>
    <li><strong>retentionDepth</strong> — Number of retained object types to track</li>
    <li><strong>alertChannels</strong> — Where to send warnings (console, webhook, file)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Viewing Reports</h2>
  <p>MemoryGuard writes periodic reports to <code>.memoryguard/reports/</code>. Open any report in the companion viewer:</p>
  <pre><code>npx memoryguard view .memoryguard/reports/latest.json</code></pre>
  <p>The viewer shows a timeline of heap snapshots with object-level retention breakdowns.</p>

  <Collapsible client:load title="Understanding the report viewer" data-testid="viewer-guide">
    <p>The report viewer has three main panels:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Timeline</strong> — A line chart showing heap usage over time, with markers at each snapshot</li>
      <li><strong>Retention Table</strong> — Lists the top object types by retained size, with growth rate indicators</li>
      <li><strong>Diff View</strong> — Compare two snapshots to see which object types grew or shrank between them</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Click any point on the timeline to load that snapshot's retention breakdown in the table below.</p>
  </Collapsible>
</Layout>
